This paper is about a computer vision task, specifically panoptic segmentation, which involves both semantic segmentation and instance segmentation. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach using attention-guided unified networks, which involves machine learning and deep learning techniques, making it also likely to belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions benchmarks and evaluation metrics, indicating that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves segmentation of both foreground and background, which may also make it relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category, which deals with segmentation and classification of text.
